 Topography information:
 ----------------------

 Topography: read_from_file                          
 Topography grid definition convention:
 cell center (scalar grid points)



 Boundary conditions:
 -------------------

                     p                    uv                                  pt

 B. bound.: p(0)     = p(1)   | uv(0)     = 0                     | pt(0)     = from soil model  
 T. bound.: p(nzt+1) = p(nzt) | uv(nzt+1) = ug(nzt+1), vg(nzt+1)  | pt(nzt+1) = pt(nzt) + dpt/dz_

                     e

 B. bound.: e(0)     = e(1)                                                                      
 T. bound.: e(nzt+1) = e(nzt) = e(nzt-1)                                                         

                     q

 B. bound.: q(0)     = from soil model                                                           
 T. bound.: q(nzt+1) = q(nzt) + dq/dz                                                            

 Bottom surface fluxes are used in diffusion terms above surface grid points


    Constant flux layer between bottom surface and first computational u,v-level:

       z_mo =   0.50 m   z0 = 0.1000 m   z0h = 0.10000 m   kappa = 0.40
       zeta value range:     -20.00 <= zeta <= 20.00
       automatic limitation of roughness lengths to 0.5 * dx/dy/dz
       Predefined surface temperature
       Predefined surface humidity


 Lateral boundaries:
       left/right:  cyclic              
       north/south: cyclic              


